    "body": "## Problem\n\nAfter commit 5cbb9d613bf6 (`fix(startup): wait for bg detection before user config`), setting `guicursor=` (empty) causes a blinking cursor in all modes. This is a regression — the cursor was steady (non-blinking) before.\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\n```\nnvim --clean --cmd 'set guicursor='\n```\n\nThe cursor blinks. Before the startup timing change, it did not.\n\n## Root cause\n\nThe compile-time `shape_table` in `cursor_shape.c` has `blinkon=400` for normal mode:\n\n```c\n{ \"normal\", 0, 0, 0, 700, 400, 250, 0, 0, \"n\", SHAPE_CURSOR + SHAPE_MOUSE },\n```\n\nDuring startup:\n\n1. `ui_refresh()` (ui.c:248) calls `ui_mode_info_set()` when the TUI attaches, marking `pending_mode_info_update = true`. At this point, `parse_shape_opt` hasn't run yet (it runs in `set_init_3`, after `.vimrc`), so `mode_style_array()` returns the **compile-time** values (`blinkon=400`).\n\n2. The new `vim.wait(100, ...)` in `defaults.lua` (for background detection) triggers `ui_flush()`, which processes the pending mode_info_update and sends the compile-time cursor data to the TUI.\n\n3. The TUI's `tui_mode_info_set` stores these shapes and calls `tui_set_mode(tui, tui->showing_mode)` (tui.c:1313). For normal mode with `blinkon=400`: DECSCUSR = `1 + (400==0 || 250==0)` = `1` → sends `\\e[1 q` (**blinking block**).\n\n4. Later, `set_init_3()` runs `parse_shape_opt()`, which clears the shape_table (`blinkon=0`) and processes `guicursor=\"\"`. With empty guicursor, `cursor_style_enabled = false`, so **no correcting DECSCUSR is sent**. The stale `\\e[1 q` persists.\n\nWith a non-empty `guicursor` (e.g. `--clean` defaults), step 4 sends `cursor_style_enabled = true` and the TUI corrects to `\\e[2 q` (steady block). The bug only manifests with `guicursor=\"\"`.\n\n## Verification\n\nCapturing escape sequences with `script` confirms:\n\n- `nvim --clean --cmd 'set guicursor='` → 1× `\\e[1 q` (blinking block), no `\\e[2 q`\n- `nvim --clean` → 1× `\\e[1 q` followed by 3× `\\e[2 q` (steady block corrects it)\n\n## Expected behavior\n\n`guicursor=\"\"` should produce a steady block cursor (no blinking), as it did before the startup timing change.\n\n## Environment\n\n- NVIM v0.12.0-dev-2454+g32e0d05d53 (Homebrew HEAD)\n- Terminal: Ghostty 1.2.3 (with `cursor-style-blink = false`)\n- macOS (Darwin 25.3.0)\n- `TERM=xterm-ghostty`",
